commit.message:
Prioritize exact matches in search results

This fixes 'string (2)' vs 'std::to_string(2)' issue (std:: has a higher
priority). To reproduce run:

    cppman 'string (2)'

cppreference.com: fix [static], [virtual]

Cut [static] or [virtual] and prepend it to the tail.

Examples to reproduce:
    https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/error/exception
    what [virtual]
    cppman 'std::exception'

    https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/string/basic_string
    npos [static]
    cppman 'std::basic_string'
Bump version to 0.5.6
Add custom headers to requests
Bump version to 0.5.5
Update index.db

Fix keywords extraction

Example to reproduce:
https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/template_argument_deduction

crawler: fix duplicate titles

Add a part of the URL's path to the titles that are not unique.
Examples:
  * std::move (algorithm)
  * std::move (utility)
  * std::to_string (string/basic_string)
  * std::to_string (utility/basic_stacktrace)
  * std::to_string (utility/stacktrace_entry)

Fix page name extraction

<h1> may span multiple lines and be uppercase.

crawler: make indexing more robust

 * handle all download errors
 * re-fetch failed pages after a round of crawling until either no
   failed pages are left or there is no progress (controlled by
   self.max_failed_retries)
 * report download failures to help with troubleshooting

Fix cplusplus.com url

http://www.cplusplus.com/reference redirects to https://cplusplus.com/reference.
This redirection is disabled when F_SAME_PATH or F_SAME_HOST is on.

crawler: encode invalid characters in urls Those characters fire http.client.InvalidURL. Example: https://cplusplus.com/reference/new/operator%20delete/

See also

crawler: use a higher-level urllib.request API

This, among other things, fixes crawler proxy support.
Fix typo

Add hint for missing groff command

fixes #144
Update Changelog
Bump version to 0.5.4

Update index.db

Fix #137, #131
Add fish completions (#133)
